IN A POLARISED world opportunities to disagree are plentiful – and frequently destructive. Host Anne McElvoy asks Adam Grant, an organisational psychologist and author of “Think Again”, why he thinks the key to arguing well is to be open-minded. They discuss whether social media erode reasoned argument, and the new breed of powerful political communicators. Plus, how does the psychology of resilience help those who are “languishing”?  Please subscribe to The Economist for full access to print, digital and audio editions: www.economist.com/podcastoffer Listen on: Apple Podcasts | Spotify | Google | Stitcher | TuneIn